What is a ReplicaSet?
Ans: A ReplicaSet ensures that a specified number of Pod replicas are always running.

Example:

Desired State = 3 Pods
Running Pods = 3

If one Pod dies:

Desired State = 3
Running Pods = 2

ReplicaSet automatically creates:

New Pod = 1
Running Pods = 3

This is called:

Self-Healing


Scenario 1: Create ReplicaSet
replicaset.yaml

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: ReplicaSet

metadata:
  name: nginx-rs

spec:
  replicas: 3

  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx

  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: nginx

    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx

Deploy:

kubectl apply -f replicaset.yaml

Verify:

kubectl get rs

Expected:

NAME       DESIRED CURRENT READY
nginx-rs   3       3       3

Check Pods:

kubectl get pods

Example:

nginx-rs-x1abc
nginx-rs-y2def
nginx-rs-z3ghi
Understanding Labels & Selectors

ReplicaSet tracks Pods using:

matchLabels:
  app: nginx

and

labels:
  app: nginx

These must match.

Think:

ReplicaSet = Manager

Labels = Employee ID Card

Selector = Employee Database Search
Part 3: Self-Healing Demo

Delete a Pod:

kubectl delete pod nginx-rs-x1abc

Watch:

kubectl get pods -w

Observe:

Old Pod Terminating

New Pod Created

Desired Count Maintained
Assignment

Delete all Pods one by one.

Observe:

ReplicaSet keeps recreating them.

Question:

Can users still access the application?

Answer:

Yes (if Service is configured properly).
